				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Alrighty, partly from reading the responses here, and reading another topic about how to create a proper NES loop, I have now solved my problem with drawing the whole background.
<br />
<br />It turned out that I was making a huge mistake - Drawing the background outside of VBlank.  After noticing that I started drawing in VBlank - sending 128 byte blocks of tile data in at a time, which is about as much as I could squeeze into a single VBlank.  So, I am drawing my whole background in roughly 7 1/2 VBlank cycles, and I am quite happy with the result, with no glitches other than unused sprites on the screen.  I think I'm going to do more searches to remember how to get rid of the phantom sprites.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

